HEADWORD: Interlineation
<hw>In`ter*lin`e*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>interlin⟦eacute⟧ation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of interlining.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is interlined; a passage, word, or line
inserted between lines already written or printed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>interlingua</ent>⟦br⟧
